note that the install.sh cannot be used on windows (maybe available on cygwin)

step:
1. git clone https://haohaolee@github.com/haohaolee/My-own-vimrc.git ~/.vim        on linux OR
   git clone https://haohaolee@github.com/haohaolee/My-own-vimrc.git ~/vimfiles    on Windows "~" points to %userprofile%
2. run sh ~/.vim/install.sh linux          on linux to install OR
   manally create a _vimrc in %userprofile% dir and write
BEGIN============================================================
fun! MySys()
   return "windows"
endfun
source ~/vimfiles/vimrc
helptags ~/vimfiles/doc

END==============================================================


